15/04/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Former Prime Minister Ivica Racan was in critical condition Saturday (April 14th), after slipping into a coma Thursday. 
Battling brain cancer, Racan stepped down as head of the opposition Social Democratic Party on Wednesday. 
He had announced his temporary withdrawal from politics in February, following his initial diagnosis. 
(Index.hr, HRT, HINA - 15/04/07; Vjesnik - 14/04/07)
